# Diamond Dependency Conflicts (Non-Blocking)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file surfaces ~10 theoretical conflicts when pip-compile flattens all deps.
# These are SAFE TO IGNORE because conflicting tools run in isolated venvs:
#   - checkov, prowler, semgrep: installed in isolated venvs via `jmo tools install`
#   - pip-audit, py-ocsf-models: dev-only packages, not shipped to users
# The flat requirements-dev.txt combines all dev deps which exposes version
# conflicts between packages that never share a Python environment in production.
# See: .claude/known-issues.md "deps-compile Diamond Dependencies" for details.

pytest
pytest-cov
pytest-split>=0.9.0  # Test sharding for CI parallelization
pytest-timeout>=2.3.0  # Safety net to prevent infinite test hangs
hypothesis
pytest-rerunfailures
pytest-xdist>=3.5.0  # Parallel test execution with -n auto
pytest-json-report>=1.5.0  # Machine-readable test output for Ralph Loop
ruff
bandit
black
pyyaml
jsonschema
pre-commit
mypy
types-PyYAML
types-tabulate
types-requests
croniter
types-croniter

# MCP Server dependencies (Feature #2: AI Remediation)
mcp[cli]>=1.0.0  # Official Anthropic MCP SDK with FastMCP framework

# Policy-as-Code dependencies (Feature #5: Policy-as-Code)
# Note: OPA binary installed separately via scripts/dev/install_tools.sh
# Python dependencies for policy integration
packaging  # For version comparison in OPA version checks

# Trend Analysis dependencies (Feature #4: Trend Analysis - v1.0.0)
scipy>=1.11.0,<1.15.0  # Mann-Kendall test; constrained for Python 3.10 compatibility
numpy>=1.24.0,<2.3.0  # Explicitly constrain numpy for Python 3.10 support

# SLSA Attestation dependencies (Feature #6: Supply Chain Attestation - v1.0.0)
sigstore>=2.0.0  # Sigstore Python SDK for keyless signing (Fulcio + Rekor)
cryptography>=41.0.0  # Cryptographic primitives for hashing and signing

# Platform-specific transitive deps pinned as top-level to stabilize cross-platform
# resolution. pip-compile on Linux will otherwise omit these, forcing CI to
# sed-inject them into the lockfile (see history: .github/workflows/ci.yml).
#
# - pywin32: Windows-only, needed by mcp[cli] on win32 hosts
# - colorama: transitive via bandit/click/pytest; omitted by Linux resolver
# - pytz: transitive via croniter; omitted by Linux resolver
pywin32 ; sys_platform == "win32"
colorama
pytz
